- The resale price is the price at which a property is sold in the secondary market;
- The average resale price is a measure of the typical resale value of properties in a given town;
- The ranking is based on the average resale price, with higher prices leading to a higher rank.

- "crown jewel" refers to the most valuable or prominent town in terms of amenities;
- "conveniences" are amenities within a 1 km radius of properties;
- "1 km radius" is the distance used to determine proximity to amenities.

- Maintenance costs are calculated differently based on property type: 10% for apartments, 15% for condos, and 20% for other types;
- "High" transport accessibility is defined as a public transport density greater than 0.5;
- "Distance" refers to the distance to a reference point or amenity;
- "Resale price" is the price at which a property is sold;
- "Profit" is calculated as the resale price minus the maintenance cost.

- "Top 5 in terms of average income" means the towns with the highest average income;
- "Lowest crime rates" means the towns with the lowest crime rates;
- "More than 5 amenities" refers to properties with more than 5 nearby amenities;
- "Viewed more than 10 times" means properties that have been accessed more than 10 times in the access logs.

